Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Channel
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The Channel component is a React Context provider that wraps all of the logic, functionality, and UI for an individual chat channel. It provides three separate contexts to its children:

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: ChannelHead
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: ChannelHead as a fixed header in DashBoard, and it integrates CreateChannel inside which needs to be used in the Chat component.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Channel List
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The ChannelList component queries an array of channel objects from the Chat API

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Chat
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The Chat component is a React Context provider that wraps the entire Web3MQ Chat application. All chat Components within the @web3mq/react-components library must be nested as children of Chat to maintain proper functionality.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: ConnectMessage
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: ConnectMessage is a global prompt component used to indicate the status of a Websocket connection,and can only be used in the chat component.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: CreateChannel
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: CreateChannel is a set of features and UI components for sending friends and creating chat rooms, it needs to get the client property through useChatContext and cannot be used alone outside the Chat component.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: DashBoard
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: AS The Tabs component, DashBoard renders ChannelList、ContactList、NotificationList and Profile by default when no props are passed, it gets showListTypeView property that the current type of tab panel  through the useChatContext, and cannot be used outside the Chat component.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: LoginModal
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: LoginModal component implements login and registration operations.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: MessageConsole
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: MessageConsole is essentially a functional component that works with user permissions. It renders the content of input or operation based on the permissions of both users in the current chat, if both permissions are passed, render the input content; if permissions are not passed show the operation content for sending friend request and follow operation.And can only be used in the chat component.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: MessageHead
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: As the fixed header in chat room, MessageHead is used to render the chat room information and provide functions, such as inviting people into a group. It must exist as the Chat and Channel subcomponent, because MessageHead needs to get the activeChannel and client properties from the context.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: MessageInput
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The MessageInput component is a React Context provider that does not inject any UI. The MessageInput renders ChatAutoComplete component by default when it does not inject the Input as the props.MessageInputmust be used in the Chat and Channel components.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: MessageList
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The MessageList component renders a scrollable list of messages. The UI for each individual message is rendered conditionally based on its message.type value. The list renders date separators, new message notifications, system messages, and standard messages containing text.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Notification
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The Notification is a component for detailed display of notification content, show content when activeNotification is set.Currently only when the notification type is system.friend_request will show the corresponding style, the future will be more extended. And must be nested as children of Chat to maintain proper functionality.This component does not need to pass any props.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: NotificationList
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: NotificationList, which renders the current list when other users send you friend requests, follow you, invite you to groups, subscribe to topics and post content. And must be nested as children of Chat to maintain proper functionality.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Notify
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: The Notify is a function component that sends notifications to users, the functions in the Notify are implemented based on the client api and can only be used in Chat.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.title: Profile
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/chatCo.description: Profile is a component that displays display userinfo.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/Intro.description: This tutorial walks you through how to use @web3mq/react-components using a sample React projects, and successfully build a chat app interface

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.title: Popover
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.description: The floating card popped by clicking or hovering.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.title: Skeleton
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.description: Skeleton provide a placeholder while you wait for content to load, or to visualize content that doesn't exist yet.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.title: Toast
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.description: toast display global messages as feedback in response to user operations.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.title: Window
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-React/utilit.description: In @web3mq/react-components, Window is used to wrap the MessageList, MessageHeader, and MessageInput components to compatibility with views.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Swift/Channe.title: Channel List
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Swift/Channe.description: The ChannelListViewController is the UI component used to display a list of channels matching the given query.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Swift/Integr.description: To get started integrating Web3MQ in your UIKit iOS app, check our Integration page

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.title: Channel
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.description: The Channel component is a Vue dependency provider that wraps all of the logic, functionality, and UI for an individual chat channel. It provides two separate Vue Provide to its children:

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.title: Channel List
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.description: The ChannelList component queries an array of channel objects from the Chat API, it subscribes internally to the channel.type event and updates the channel list data based on it.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.title: Message Input
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.description: The MessageInput component is the method provider, such as send messages.

Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.title: MessageList
Web3MQ-UI-Components/Web3MQ-Vue/chatComp.description: The MessageList component renders a scrollable list of messages. The UI for each individual message is rendered conditionally based on its message.type value. The list renders standard messages.
